<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="324" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,534,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,350,959,985]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Description.</emphasis>
Total length 1.10–1.20 mm. Body of pale testaceous colour, clearly shiny, with superficial microsculpture on all integuments. Head slightly wider than pronotum, with moderately rounded sides and only slightly outlined frontal carinas; punctuation poor; labrum (
<figureCitation box="[905,989,1037,1063]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–26" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1788,1812]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,278,1760]" captionTargetId="figure-132@9.[151,1436,274,1763]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–26. Leptotyphlus spp., scale bars 0.05 mm. 18–20. Leptotyphlus nardii sp. nov. (paratype, Nebida). 18. Labrum in dorsal view. 19. Right mandible in dorsal view. 20. Female genital armature in ventral view. 21–23. Leptotyphlus villacidrinus sp. nov. (paratype, Villacidro). 21. Labrum in dorsal view. 22. Right mandible in dorsal view. 23. Female genital armature of Leptotyphlus villacidrinus sp. nov. (paratype, Villacidro) in ventral view. 24–26. Leptotyphlus minator sp. nov. (paratype, Gutturu di Monte Nieddu). 24. Female genital armature in ventral view. 25. Labrum in dorsal view. 26. Right mandible in dorsal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) with three weakly developed median teeth; mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[366,453,1076,1102]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–26" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1788,1812]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,278,1760]" captionTargetId="figure-132@9.[151,1436,274,1763]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–26. Leptotyphlus spp., scale bars 0.05 mm. 18–20. Leptotyphlus nardii sp. nov. (paratype, Nebida). 18. Labrum in dorsal view. 19. Right mandible in dorsal view. 20. Female genital armature in ventral view. 21–23. Leptotyphlus villacidrinus sp. nov. (paratype, Villacidro). 21. Labrum in dorsal view. 22. Right mandible in dorsal view. 23. Female genital armature of Leptotyphlus villacidrinus sp. nov. (paratype, Villacidro) in ventral view. 24–26. Leptotyphlus minator sp. nov. (paratype, Gutturu di Monte Nieddu). 24. Female genital armature in ventral view. 25. Labrum in dorsal view. 26. Right mandible in dorsal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) bifid with robust retinaculum and premolar tooth; antennae relatively short, just longer than head. Pronotum slightly longer than wide, with two longitudinal superficial grooves, slightly converging anteriorly; punctuation minute and sparser than on head. Elytral punctuation imperceptible. Convexity of abdominal tergites normal. Aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[819,904,1192,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–17" captionStartId="8.[151,271,995,1019]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,241,965]" captionTargetId="figure-374@8.[151,1436,235,969]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–17. Male copulatory organ of Leptotyphlus spp. in lateral view, scale bars: 0.05 mm. 15. Leptotyphlus villacidrinus sp. nov. (paratype, Villacidro). 16. Leptotyphlus nardii sp. nov. (paratype, Nebida). 17. Leptotyphlus minator sp. nov. (paratype, Nebida)." pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
, lying on the left side of the abdomen, with a robust and arched dorsal copulatory piece; sternal lamina distally divided into two branches; tip of ventral branch in lateral view with a distinct downturned lobiform appendix. Female genital armature asymmetrical, structured as in 
<figureCitation box="[337,424,1308,1334]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–26" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1788,1812]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,278,1760]" captionTargetId="figure-132@9.[151,1436,274,1763]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18–26. Leptotyphlus spp., scale bars 0.05 mm. 18–20. Leptotyphlus nardii sp. nov. (paratype, Nebida). 18. Labrum in dorsal view. 19. Right mandible in dorsal view. 20. Female genital armature in ventral view. 21–23. Leptotyphlus villacidrinus sp. nov. (paratype, Villacidro). 21. Labrum in dorsal view. 22. Right mandible in dorsal view. 23. Female genital armature of Leptotyphlus villacidrinus sp. nov. (paratype, Villacidro) in ventral view. 24–26. Leptotyphlus minator sp. nov. (paratype, Gutturu di Monte Nieddu). 24. Female genital armature in ventral view. 25. Labrum in dorsal view. 26. Right mandible in dorsal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,534,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,371,1346,1372]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Observations.</emphasis>
As hinted in the diagnosis, the phyletic relationships of the new species seem complex. This forced us to describe the new species and the following two without subgeneric assignment. Besides, the subdivision of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fauvel" authorityYear="1874" box="[335,493,1424,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[335,493,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Leptotyphlus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still debated: 
<bibRefCitation author="Herman, L. H." box="[699,887,1424,1450]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" pagination="1807 - 2440" refId="ref12405" refString="Herman, L. H. (2001) Catalog of the Staphylinidae (Insecta: Coleoptera). 1758 to the end of the second millenium. 4. Staphylininae group (part 1), Euaesthetinae, Leptotyphlinae, Megalopsidinae, Oxyporinae, Pseudopsinae, Solieriinae, Steninae. Bullettin of the American Museum of Natural History, 265, 1807 - 2440." type="journal article" year="2001">Herman (2001)</bibRefCitation>
considers all described subgenera simply as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fauvel" authorityYear="1874" box="[312,465,1463,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[312,465,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Leptotyphlus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas 
<bibRefCitation author="Smetana, A." box="[585,780,1462,1488]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" refId="ref13998" refString="Smetana, A. (2004 a) Fauna Europaea: Staphylinidae Leptotyphlinae. In: Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. (Ed.), Fauna Europaea: Coleoptera 1, Beetles. Fauna Europaea version 1.1, available at http: // www. faunaeur. org [accessed September 2009 as version 1.3 of April 19 th 2007.]" type="url" year="2004">
Smetana (2004 
<bibRefCitation author="Smetana, A." box="[767,780,1462,1488]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" refId="ref14062" refString="Smetana, A. (2004 b) Staphylinidae Leptotyphlinae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 568 - 578." type="book" year="2004">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 2004b) continues to follow the classic arrangement of the genus proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Coiffait, H." box="[430,611,1501,1527]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" pagination="1 - 651" refId="ref11852" refString="Coiffait, H. (1972) Coleopteres Staphylinidae de la region palearctique occidentale. I. Generalites, Sousfamilles: Xantholininae et Leptotyphlinae. Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, Suppl. 2 (2), 1 - 651." type="journal article" year="1972">Coiffait (1972)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pace R. &amp; Fauna d'Italia, XXXIV" box="[671,819,1501,1527]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" refId="ref13459" refString="Pace R., (1996). Fauna d'Italia, XXXIV. Coleoptera Staphylinidae Leptotyphlinae. Calderini, Bologna, 328 pp." type="book" year="1996">Pace (1996)</bibRefCitation>
. In our opinion the characters proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Coiffait, H." pageId="7" pageNumber="324" pagination="1 - 651" refId="ref11852" refString="Coiffait, H. (1972) Coleopteres Staphylinidae de la region palearctique occidentale. I. Generalites, Sousfamilles: Xantholininae et Leptotyphlinae. Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, Suppl. 2 (2), 1 - 651." type="journal article" year="1972">Coiffait (1972)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pace R. &amp; Fauna d'Italia, XXXIV" box="[290,434,1540,1566]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" refId="ref13459" refString="Pace R., (1996). Fauna d'Italia, XXXIV. Coleoptera Staphylinidae Leptotyphlinae. Calderini, Bologna, 328 pp." type="book" year="1996">Pace (1996)</bibRefCitation>
sometimes cause the placement of clearly allied species within separate subgenera, like in the emblematic case of the new species described above. 
<taxonomicName authority="Fancello &amp; Hernando &amp; Leo, 2009" authorityName="Fancello &amp; Hernando &amp; Leo" authorityYear="2009" box="[904,1132,1579,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nardii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[904,1132,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Leptotyphlus nardii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1140,1230,1578,1604]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
should indeed be ascribed to subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1955" box="[403,568,1617,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stigmotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[403,568,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Stigmotyphlus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the asymmetrical female genital armature and for the aedeagus with a large coil-shaped dorsal copulatory piece; however, from further examination it appears that 
<taxonomicName authority="Fancello &amp; Hernando &amp; Leo, 2009" authorityName="Fancello &amp; Hernando &amp; Leo" authorityYear="2009" box="[1237,1338,1656,1682]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nardii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1237,1253,1656,1681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1268,1338,1656,1681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">nardii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,1656,1682]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is clearly related to some peninsular species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1955" box="[715,881,1695,1720]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stigmotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[715,881,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Stigmotyphlus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="1973" box="[966,1113,1694,1720]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lessinicus">
<emphasis box="[966,982,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[998,1113,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">lessinicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group (
<taxonomicName authority="Pace, 1977" authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="1977" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molisensis">
<emphasis box="[1210,1226,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1242,1365,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">molisensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pace, R." pageId="7" pageNumber="324" pagination="155 - 201" refId="ref13312" refString="Pace, R. (1977) Dodici nuove specie di Leptotyphlinae dell'Italia peninsulare (Coleoptera Staphylinidae). Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 4, 155 - 201." type="journal article" year="1977">Pace, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Pace, 1977" authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="1977" box="[267,557,1733,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="campanus">
<emphasis box="[267,283,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[299,418,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">campanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pace, R." box="[426,557,1733,1759]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" pagination="155 - 201" refId="ref13312" refString="Pace, R. (1977) Dodici nuove specie di Leptotyphlinae dell'Italia peninsulare (Coleoptera Staphylinidae). Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 4, 155 - 201." type="journal article" year="1977">Pace, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, extremely similar with regard to all structures of the copulatory organ: 
<emphasis box="[1407,1437,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">cf.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pace, R." box="[151,276,1772,1798]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" pagination="155 - 201" refId="ref13312" refString="Pace, R. (1977) Dodici nuove specie di Leptotyphlinae dell'Italia peninsulare (Coleoptera Staphylinidae). Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 4, 155 - 201." type="journal article" year="1977">Pace 1977</bibRefCitation>
, figs 190–191), and to Sardo-Corsican species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fauvel" authorityYear="1874" box="[865,1016,1772,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptotyphlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[865,1016,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Leptotyphlus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1025,1087,1772,1798]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1955" box="[1172,1295,1772,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Brachyceridae" genus="Raymondiellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sardous">
<emphasis box="[1172,1188,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1203,1295,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">sardous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, also with a coil-shaped dorsal copulatory piece (
<emphasis box="[663,684,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">cf</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pace R. &amp; Fauna d'Italia, XXXIV" box="[699,823,1810,1836]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" refId="ref13459" refString="Pace R., (1996). Fauna d'Italia, XXXIV. Coleoptera Staphylinidae Leptotyphlinae. Calderini, Bologna, 328 pp." type="book" year="1996">Pace 1996</bibRefCitation>
, figs 163–165).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,534,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,407,1848,1874]" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Ecological notes.</emphasis>
The species was collected by washing soil in both Mediterranean maquis with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Pistacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lentiscus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Pistacia lentiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
dominance and 
<taxonomicName box="[451,600,1888,1913]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ilex">
<emphasis box="[451,600,1888,1913]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Quercus ilex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
woodland. Collecting sites are situated on Palaeozoic limestone soils. The following endogean beetles were collected together with the new species: 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1285,1927,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Batysciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="damryi">
<emphasis box="[1071,1285,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Batysciola damryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1821" box="[1300,1423,1926,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Leiodidae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Belon" authorityYear="1882" box="[151,401,1965,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" genus="Langelandia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reitteri">
<emphasis box="[151,401,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Langelandia reitteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Solier" authorityYear="1834" box="[420,568,1965,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Zopheridae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[590,757,1965,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Torneuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[590,713,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Torneuma</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[775,957,1965,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Curculionidae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perris" authorityYear="1869" box="[981,1235,1965,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Brachyceridae" genus="Alaocyba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinulata">
<emphasis box="[981,1235,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Alaocyba carinulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="sardous" authorityName="sardous (Perris" authorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Brachyceridae" genus="Raymondiellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sardous" subSpecies="sardous">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="324">Raymondiellus sardous sardous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fancello &amp; Hernando &amp; Leo" authorityYear="2009" box="[357,602,2004,2030]" class="Insecta" family="Raymondionymidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Raymondionymidae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
